label.value: dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product

value.value: A dengue virus genome polyprotein, N-glycosylated form that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a structural protein processed at the N-terminal end of the dengue virus RNA genome.

definition.value: Category=modification. Requested by=IDODEN. Capsid protein C is a highly basic alpha-helical protein of about 100 amino acid residues that forms an emphipathic homodimer to encapsidate the viral genome and to interact with viral membranes [PMID:23673222, PRO:ES].

value.value: A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from its precursor form prM protein on the surface of immature dengue virus by host protease during virion maturation.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from its precursor prM and localizes to the endoplasmic reticulum and forms oligomers.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a structural protein containing two alpha-helices (EH1 and EH2) at the C-terminus and two transmembrane domains (ET1 and ET2) of the dengue virus RNA genome. It contains two N-linked glycosylation sites, at Asn-67 and Asn-153. Example: UniProtKB:P29990, 281-775, Asn-347/Asn-433, MOD:00160.

definition.value: Category=modification. Requested by=IDODEN. The E protein is responsible for eliciting the majority of the protective dengue virus antibody response. It covers the virion surface arranged in anti-parallel dimers containing three structural and antigenic domains [PMID:22709350, PRO:ES].

value.value: A protein-containing complex that involves the initial assembly of the dengue virion as an immature particle which contains prM noncovalently associated with E in a heterodimeric complex. It contains N-linked glycosylation sites at Asn-347, Asn-433, Asn-183. UniProtKB:P29990, 115-775, Asn-183/Asn-347/Asn-433, MOD:00160.

definition.value: Category=complex. Requested by=IDODEN. In the prME heterodimer, prM prevents an irreversible conformational change of E during virus secretion through acidified sorting compartments. Proteolysis of prM leads to the formation of homodimeric forms of E in virus particles before their release from the cell. [PMID:10590151, PRO:ES].

value.value: A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is the N-terminal most non-structural protein within the dengue virus genome polyprotein. Example: UniProtKB:P29990, 776-1127, Asn-905/Asn-982, MOD:00160.

definition.value: Category=modification. Requested by=IDODEN. NS1 is a secreted glycoprotein that is absent from viral particles but accumulates in the supernatant and on the plasma membrane of cells during infection. Because it derives from a glycosylated precursor it includes two N-glycosylated residues at Asn-130 and Asn-207. [PMID:18052531, PRO:ES].

value.value: A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a non-structural protein encoded by the dengue virus RNA genome and a component of the viral replication complex.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that consists of 188 amino acids at the N-terminal end of NS2A.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a non-structural protein encoded by the dengue virus RNA genome containing a conserved hydrophilic domain necessary for protease activity in cleavage of the dengue virus genome polyprotein, N-glycosylated form.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a non-structural, multifunctional protein encoded by the dengue virus RNA genome with a serine protease domain.

A protein-containing complex consisting of NS3 which has a serine protease domain that requires the conserved hydrophilic domain of NS2B for protease activity in cleavage of the dengue virus genome polyprotein, N-glycosylated form at sites following two basic amino acids.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a highly hydrophobic non-structural protein encoded by the dengue virus RNA genome that associates with membranes via 4 internal hydrophobic regions which are all able to mediate membrane targeting of a cytosolic reporter protein.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is the C-terminal region of NS4A serving as a signal sequence for the translocation of the adjacent NS4B into the endoplasmic reticulum (ER) lumen.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a precursor of NS4B.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a highly hydrophobic transmembrane non-structural protein encoded by the dengue virus RNA genome which is, in part, responsible for the membrane arrangements leading to the formation of the viral replication complex.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a precursor of NS5.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a large non-structural protein encoded by the dengue virus RNA genome containing a methyltransferase (MTase) domain and an RNA dependent RNA polymerase (POL) domain that possesses a capping enzyme.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is derived from dengue virus genome polyprotein, glycosylated form and that consists only of the C (capsid) protein and the prM (pre-membrane) structural proteins of the dengue virus genome polyprotein. It has a single N-linked glycosylation site at position Asn-69. Example: UniProtKB:P29990, 1-280, Asn-183, MOD:00160.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is a product of the cleavage of C-prM by host signalase. It has a single N-linked glycosylation site at position Asn-69. Example: UniProtKB:P29990, 115-280, Asn-183, MOD:00160.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is derived from dengue virus genome polyprotein, N-glycosylated form and that contains the entire non-structural region of the dengue virus genome polyprotein only and is responsible for directing viral genomic RNA replication, including synthesizing negative- and positive-strand RNAs and forming the viral RNA cap structure. It consists of NS1, NS2A, NS3, NS4A, 2K, NS4B, and NS5.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from NS12345 by the two-component proteinase NS2B-NS3 at the NS2B-NS3 site consisting of NS3, NS4A, NS4B, and NS5.

definition.value: Category=modification. Requested by=IDODEN. Cleavage at the NS2A-NS2B site was also mediated by the NS2B-NS3 protease, while the NS1-NS2A site was mediated by host cell-derived protease.

value.value: A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from NS345 by the two-component proteinase NS2B-NS3 at the NS3-NS4A site consisting of NS4A, 2K, NS4B, and NS5.

definition.value: Category=modification. Requested by=IDODEN. The polyprotein NS4A-NS4B-NS5 was cleaved at the NS4A/NS4B junction in the absence of other dengue virus functions.

value.value: A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from NS4A-NS4B-NS5 by the two-component proteinase NS2B-NS3 at the NS4B-NS5 sites consisting of NS4A, 2K, and NS4B.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that assists in the processing of NS4AB consisting of 2K and NS4B.

A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from NS4A-NS4B-NS5 at the NS4A-NS4B site consisting of NS4B and NS5, which is believed to be mediated by a host cell signal peptidase.
A CD14 molecule, signal peptide removed form that lacks the propeptide. Example: UniProtKB:P08571, 20-345.

label.value: CD14 molecule cleaved and soluble form

value.value: A CD14 molecule, signal peptide removed form that has been processed by proteolytic cleavage to yield the N-terminal domain lacking a GPI-anchor.

label.value: CD14 molecule cleaved and soluble form (mouse)

value.value: A CD14 molecule cleaved and soluble form in mouse.

A presenilin-2 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q61144-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A presenilin-2 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q61144-2 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This isoform contains N-terminal fragment (NTF) and hydrophilic loop domain, but not C-terminal fragment (CTF).
A presenilin-2 isoform PS2beta that is encoded in the genome of human.

definition.value: Category=organism-sequence. Note: The corresponding entry E5RJ26 has been withdrawn from UniProtKB.

value.value: A presenilin-2 that is a translation product of some mRNA produced by alternative promoter usage, giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by residues 298 to 448 in UniProtKB:Q61144 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A presenilin-2 isoform PS2short that is encoded in the genome of mouse. UniProtKB:Q61144-1, 298-448.

definition.value: Category=organism-sequence. Although generated by different means, this form is (by sequence) identical to PR:000036890 presenilin-2 isoform 1 CTF subunit (mouse).

value.value: A catenin beta-1 that has been phosphorylated on the Tyr residue in the motif NLINYQDD located upstream of the first ARM repeat. Example: UniProtKB:Q02248, Tyr-142, MOD:00048.
A catenin beta-1 phosphorylated 1 in mouse. UniProtKB:Q02248, Tyr-142, MOD:00048.

definition.value: Category=organism-modification. Kinase=("FER"; PR:P16591; Tyr-142). Kinase=("FYN"; PR:P06241; Tyr-142). Note: In vitro.

value.value: A catenin beta-1 isoform 1 that has been phosphorylated on two Ser residues in the cAMP-dependent protein kinase phosphorylation consensus sites, [RK](2)-x-[ST] located towards the C-terminal region. Example: UniProtKB:P35222-1, Ser-552/Ser-675, MOD:00046.
A catenin beta-1 isoform 1 phosphorylated 5 in human. UniProtKB:P35222-1, Ser-552/Ser-675, MOD:00046.

definition.value: Category=organism-modification. Kinase=("PKA"; PR:000029188; Ser-552/Ser-675). Note: In vitro, in vivo.

value.value: A neurexin-2 that is translated from the upstream promoter, yielding proteins with EGF-like domains.
A neurexin-2 that is translated from the downstream promoter, yielding proteins lacking EGF-like domains.
A neurexin-3 that is translated from the upstream promoter, yielding proteins with EGF-like domains.
A neurexin-3 that is translated from the downstream promoter, yielding proteins lacking EGF-like domains.
A CALCA gene translation product that is encoded in the genome of rat.
A CALCA gene translation product that is encoded in the genome of chicken.

A catenin beta-1 isoform 1 that lacks phosphorylation at positions equivalent to Ser-552 and Ser-675 of the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P35222-1. Example: UniProtKB:P35222-1, Ser-552/Ser-675, PR:000026291.
A catenin beta-1 isoform 1 unphosphorylated 1 in human. UniProtKB:P35222-1, Ser-552/Ser-675, PR:000026291.
A dengue virus genome polyprotein proteolytic cleavage product that is cleaved from NS12345 by the two-component protease NS2B-NS3 at the NS2A-NS2B and NS3-NS4 sites and consists of NS2B and NS3.

definition.value: Category=modification. Requested by=IDODEN. Analysis of polyprotein processing in vivo established that the NS3 protease, as a heterodimeric complex with the viral activator protein NS2B, catalyzes the cis cleavage of NS2A-NS2B and NS2B-NS3, as well as the trans cleavage of NS3-NS4A and NS4B-NS5 sites in the polyprotein. [PMID:10744671, PRO:ES]
